# Database Rules

## Supabase Clients

Two clients in `lib/supabase.ts`:
- `supabase` — anon/public key, respects RLS. Used in client components.
- `supabaseAdmin` — service role key, bypasses RLS. Used in API routes.

Server components use `lib/supabase/server.ts` → `createClient()`.

## Tables (key ones)

| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `admin_profile` | Single row with business info |
| `admin_settings` | Key-value settings store |
| `bookings` | Customer bookings with deposits |
| `customers` | Customer records |
| `payments` | Payment records linked to bookings |
| `services` | Treatment services |
| `pricing_cards` | Pricing display cards |
| `gallery` | Before/after gallery items |
| `reviews` | Customer reviews |
| `blog_posts` | Blog content |
| `team` | Team members |
| `working_hours` | Business hours per day |
| `discount_codes` | Customer discount codes |
| `discount_groups` | Service discount groups |
| `day_off_periods` | Holiday/day-off periods |

## Tables That Do NOT Exist

- `admin_areas_cover` — Do NOT query this table. It will error.

## Bookings Table Columns

Core: `id`, `customer_id`, `customer_name`, `customer_email`, `customer_phone`, `service`, `date`, `time`, `status`, `payment_status`, `amount`

Deposit support: `total_amount`, `amount_paid`, `remaining_amount`, `payment_type` ('full'|'deposit'), `payment_method` ('cash'|'card'|'cash_and_card')

Extra: `booking_number`, `team_member_id`, `service_duration_minutes`, `address`, `notes`, `reminder_24h_sent`, `reminder_1h_sent`, `followup_sent`

## Migrations

- Location: `supabase/migrations/`
- Naming: `YYYYMMDD_description.sql`
- Always use `IF NOT EXISTS` / `IF EXISTS` for safety
- Backfill existing data when adding columns
- Apply via Supabase Dashboard SQL Editor (CLI not linked)
